    <section xml:id="overview" xreflabel="Overview">
        <title>Overview</title>
        <para>Welcome to ${project.parent.name} ${project.version}! </para>
        <para>The KHR Team is happy to announce the release of version 2.1 of Kuali Human Resources (KHR).  
            This release is an exciting milestone in the short history of KHR, with our new Position Management
            module we are releasing the first piece of our core, traditional human resources modules! </para>
        <section>
            <title>Impacting Changes and Release Highlights</title>
            <para>This version of KHR is a minor release consisting new modules, bug fixes, and
                items needed by Kuali application partners.</para>
            <para>
                <itemizedlist>
                    <title>Position Management:</title>
                    <listitem><para>New! Position Management Module</para></listitem>
                </itemizedlist>
            </para>
            <para>
                <itemizedlist>
                    <title>Core:</title>
                    <listitem><para>Bug fixes</para></listitem>
                </itemizedlist>
            </para>
            <para>
                <itemizedlist>
                    <title>Timekeeping and Leave Management:</title>
                    <listitem><para>AngularJS mobile swipe application</para></listitem>
                </itemizedlist>
            </para>
            <para>
                <itemizedlist>
                    <title>Leave Management:</title>
                    <listitem><para>Bug fixes</para></listitem>
                </itemizedlist>
            </para>
        </section>
        <section>
            <title>Download</title>
            <para>KHR ${project.version} can be downloaded from the Kuali website at <link
                    xlink:show="new" xlink:href="http://www.kuali.org/download/kpme"
                    >http://www.kuali.org/download/kpme</link>.</para>
            <para>There is a single zip file which contains both the source and binaries.  Please read the Installation Guide for
                more details on setup of these downloads</para>
            <para>Applications can also consume KHR from the maven site at <link
                    xlink:href="http://search.maven.org/#search|ga|1|org.kuali.kpme"
                    >http://search.maven.org/#search|ga|1|org.kuali.kpme</link>.</para>
        </section>
        <section>
            <title>Documentation</title>
            <para>API Documentation can be found at <link xlink:show="new" xlink:href="http://site.kuali.org/kpme/${project.version}/apidocs/index.html">http://site.kuali.org/kpme/${project.version}/apidocs/index.html</link></para>
            <para>Formal documentation can be found at <link xlink:show="new"
                                                             xlink:href="http://site.kuali.org/kpme/${project.version}/reference/html/index.html"
                    >http://site.kuali.org/kpme/${project.version}/reference/html/index.html</link>.
                This documentation is still in the process of review and update  which will continue
                through subsequent releases, so please follow the notes in each document to report
                any outdated information.</para>
        </section>
        <section>
            <title>Contact</title>
            <para>If you encounter any difficulty, please don't hesitate to contact the KHR team on
                our public collaboration mailing list at <email>kpme.tech.collab@kuali.org</email>.
                Please indicate that you are using the ${project.version} version of KHR.</para>
        </section>
    </section>
